{[ROLE leader][STAGE pre-lead]
Lead the \HK. With \HKQJT9 you hold a powerful sequence; the king is the top of that touching run and the right attacking lead against notrump.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE auction-end]
In 3\N I count four diamond tricks off \DAKJ opposite the \DQ, one heart from the \HA, and spades develop to four once I knock out the \SA, which reaches nine. The danger is hearts: my only stopper is the \HA, so winning early and later losing the lead to West lets the hearts cash. I hold up the heart to strip East, then establish spades, conceding the lead to the safe hand.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-lead]
West led the \HK, top of what looks like a long, solid sequence, so West rates to hold the \HQJ and length. I duck the first two hearts and take the \HA on the third, leaving East with no heart to return. Then I force out the \SA: four spade tricks added to four diamonds and the heart make nine. East holds the \SA, and that is the safe hand, because by then West's hearts are cut off.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-play]
Four ready diamonds plus the developed spades gave nine, but only the hold-up in hearts kept West from cashing out first. Duck the lone stopper, then build the long suit and lose the lead safely; that sequence is the whole hand. Very well played.}
